EPS for The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (ULTI) Expected At $0.21; Ep Wealth Advisors Lowered By $378,185 Its Simpson Manufacturing Co (SSD) Stake

July 27, 2017 - By Peter Erickson

Ep Wealth Advisors Inc decreased Simpson Manufacturing Co Inc (SSD) stake by 2.53% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Ep Wealth Advisors Inc sold 8,795 shares as Simpson Manufacturing Co Inc (SSD)’s stock declined 7.58%. The Ep Wealth Advisors Inc holds 338,514 shares with $14.81M value, down from 347,309 last quarter. Simpson Manufacturing Co Inc now has $2.11B valuation. The stock decreased 0.54% or $0.24 during the last trading session, reaching $43.88. About shares traded. Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD) has risen 9.03% since July 27, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 7.67% the S&P500.
 Analysts expect The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) to report $0.21 EPS on August, 1 after the close.They anticipate $0.14 EPS change or 200.00% from last quarter’s $0.07 EPS. ULTI’s profit would be $6.36M giving it 272.39 P/E if the $0.21 EPS is correct. After having $0.27 EPS previously, The Ultimate Software Group, Inc.’s analysts see -22.22% EPS growth. The stock decreased 1.39% or $3.22 during the last trading session, reaching $228.81. About shares traded. The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) has risen 10.74% since July 27, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 5.96% the S&P500.







The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. is a cloud well-known provider of people management solutions, referred to as human capital management (HCM). The company has market cap of $6.93 billion. The Company’s UltiPro product suite (UltiPro) is an engaging solution that has human resources (HR), payroll and benefits management. It has a 225.96 P/E ratio. As of December 31, 2016, UltiPro included global people management, available in 14 languages with more than 35 country-specific localizations.
Investors sentiment decreased to 0.88 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.14, from 1.02 in 2016Q3. It dived, as 32 investors sold The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. shares while 111 reduced holdings. 40 funds opened positions while 86 raised stakes. 29.20 million shares or 3.90% more from 28.10 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Timessquare Cap Mngmt Ltd Liability owns 804,205 shares for 0.98% of their portfolio. Artisan Ptnrs Limited Partnership holds 0.13% or 344,434 shares. Jpmorgan Chase And holds 53,511 shares or 0% of its portfolio. Blackrock Institutional Na holds 0.02% or 904,868 shares. Lpl Ltd Company invested in 10,896 shares. Capstone Asset Communications stated it has 0.02% of its portfolio in The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI). Boothbay Fund Ltd Limited Liability Company reported 1,393 shares. Evercore Wealth Mngmt Limited Liability Corporation owns 17 shares. Stifel holds 7,893 shares. State Treasurer State Of Michigan, a Michigan-based fund reported 11,700 shares. Tiedemann Wealth Mngmt Ltd Liability Company invested 0.06% of its portfolio in The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI). State Teachers Retirement Sys accumulated 29,918 shares. Kcg Holdings Incorporated has 4,300 shares. Wealthtrust has invested 0.01% in The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI). Tiverton Asset Mngmt Ltd holds 0.04% in The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) or 3,456 shares.
Since February 8, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 11 insider sales for $29.29 million activity. Leiter Alois T sold $345,520 worth of stock. $39,317 worth of The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) was sold by YANOVER ROBERT. $561,817 worth of The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) was sold by Swick Gregory. The insider Rogers Adam sold $2.89 million. $8.64 million worth of The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) was sold by SCHERR SCOTT. $3.60 million worth of The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) shares were sold by SCHERR MARC D. Shares for $264,003 were sold by PUTTEN LEROY VANDER on Friday, February 17.
Among 18 analysts covering Ultimate Software (NASDAQ:ULTI), 15 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 3 Hold. Therefore 83% are positive. Ultimate Software had 26 analyst reports since October 22, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was initiated by UBS on Tuesday, April 19 with “Buy”. The firm has “Outperform” rating given on Wednesday, October 28 by Northland Capital. Piper Jaffray reinitiated the shares of ULTI in report on Wednesday, June 1 with “Overweight” rating. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Wednesday, October 28 by Stifel Nicolaus. On Thursday, April 28 the stock rating was maintained by Wedbush with “Neutral”. The stock has “Outperform” rating by RBC Capital Markets on Thursday, October 22. The company was maintained on Wednesday, October 28 by Deutsche Bank. The rating was maintained by FBR Capital with “Mkt Perform” on Wednesday, October 28. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Monday, June 26 by SunTrust. The stock of The Ultimate Software Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ULTI) earned “Buy” rating by TH Capital on Wednesday, October 28.
Ep Wealth Advisors Inc increased Oracle Corp (NYSE:ORCL) stake by 16,575 shares to 298,726 valued at $10.25 million in 2016Q4. It also upped Ishares Tr (IWP) stake by 11,462 shares and now owns 15,330 shares. Accenture Plc Ireland (NYSE:ACN) was raised too. 
Investors sentiment increased to 1.82 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.82, from 1 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 4 investors sold SSD shares while 51 reduced holdings. 37 funds opened positions while 63 raised stakes. 37.97 million shares or 1.16% less from 38.42 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Comerica National Bank reported 43,389 shares. Thrivent For Lutherans reported 0% stake. Parkside Bank & Trust & Tru reported 0% in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD). Strs Ohio has invested 0.02% of its portfolio in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD). First Advsr Ltd Partnership invested in 0% or 29,627 shares. Crow Point Partners Limited Company has invested 0% in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD). The Pennsylvania-based Vanguard Inc has invested 0.01% in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD). Moreover, Sg Americas Limited Liability Company has 0.01% invested in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD). Susquehanna International Gru Llp reported 0% in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD). Mason Street Advsrs Limited Co invested in 0.01% or 8,831 shares. Ariel Invests Limited Liability Corporation has 1.90M shares for 0.98% of their portfolio. Brown Brothers Harriman And holds 0% or 1,500 shares in its portfolio. Louisiana State Employees Retirement Sys holds 0.04% in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD) or 16,200 shares. Citigroup has invested 0.01% in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD). Victory Cap Mgmt has invested 0% in Simpson Manufacturing Co, Inc. (NYSE:SSD).


