FAQs


What is your approach to financial planning?
We start by listening. Before any advice is given, it is essential that we understand what is important to you. Together, we review your personal balance sheet, risk tolerance and profit and loss statement. Once we understand your complete picture we can effectively implement the financial vehicles to work toward accomplishing your goals.


What services do you offer?
	Our services include:
	Financial Planning
	Investment Management
	Retirement Planning
	Tax Planning
	Estate Planning
	Planning for Widowhood
	Divorce Planning
	Business Planning



How many clients do you currently manage?
About 1600.


Will you be the only person working with me?
Your advisor will be your primary contact, however advisors have a skilled team to help with daily tasks you may also contact. 


How are you compensated? How will I pay for your services?
We charge a management fee each quarter. The fee reflects a set percentage of the total account.




FAQs


What is your approach to financial planning?
We start by listening. Before any advice is given, it is essential that we understand what is important to you. Together, we review your personal balance sheet, risk tolerance and profit and loss statement. Once we understand your complete picture we can effectively implement the financial vehicles to work toward accomplishing your goals.


What services do you offer?
	Our services include:
	Financial Planning
	Investment Management
	Retirement Planning
	Tax Planning
	Estate Planning
	Planning for Widowhood
	Divorce Planning
	Business Planning



How many clients do you currently manage?
About 1600.


Will you be the only person working with me?
Your advisor will be your primary contact, however advisors have a skilled team to help with daily tasks you may also contact. 


How are you compensated? How will I pay for your services?
We charge a management fee each quarter. The fee reflects a set percentage of the total account.


If you are going to manage my account, will you obtain my permission every time you buy or sell something?
EP Wealth offers two options that depend on your preferred involvement: discretionary and non-discretionary. Discretionary accounts allow us to make trades based on your goals without your permission. Non-discretionary accounts require permission before trades.


How much risk should I be willing to take?
Your risk tolerance is a personal preference and will depend on the financial objectives set between you and your advisor.


Have you ever been charged with any breaches?
No


Do you provide a free initial consultation?
Yes


Why should I choose you as my financial advisor?
Over the years, we have found that the people who choose to work with EP Wealth Advisors are looking for an intelligent approach, not formulaic precepts. We stress flexibility and creative thinking. We are committed to empowering our clients with the knowledge necessary to make informed financial decisions based on clearly assessing their position relative to their goals.




